Instllation and configuration of Virtual Environment and Flask libraries

1) create a folder called flasktutorial
2) open the follder flasktutorial inside VScode
3) Go tot terminal and run the command 'python -m venv virtual'
4) you can see tgr virtual folder is created
5) to activate the virtual environment 'cd virtual\scripts
6) type 'activate'
7) You can see the (virtual) current working folder path
8) let us install flask libraries inside the virtual environment
9) type cd .. and cd ..
10) now you will be inside flasktutorial
11) now type pip install flask
12) This previous command will install all the necessarry libraries inside the virtual \lib\site-packages folder
13) To come out of virtual environment
14) Type cd virtual
15) Type cd Scripts
16) Typre deactivate
